<br>
Sorry was dealing with it generically, I only have MC1 atm (2 yellow aa from MC2, but that isn't going to make or break me).  ATM with MC1, KeI and FT3, I am getting about 1% mana per tick while meding (of course theres a few ticks here and there at 2%). Naked with no KeI and before I had MC1, it was 1%/tick solid.  Either way it was close to 10 minute to med from oom to FM.  Add an extra lvl to it, along with some uber items and it WILL take LONGER to med. <br>
<br>
I know my gear isn't exactly top end, I don't really care about my gear ATM as it essensially does little for me.  Even if you only add 1k in mana items, your adding 20 ticks to your med time (assuming mana regen at 50/tick-KeI +14, Med+ 20, MC3 +3, FT15 +15, inate +1, TPP +3=56mana/tick?), thats 2 more minutes of meditating WITH all those mind buffs.  Without them you'd be looking at 4+ minutes more med time.  Of course one could get more int and more +mana gear (as some of the profiles I have looked up here would make my mana pool seem small).  Taking all that into consideration, it would be concievable that JT, RaZ, Wezloc, Obie, Silverblade, Etc would possibly have to meditate for 10+minutes with all the mind candy available (more so JT).  <br>
<br>
Your comment is so vague with no considerations for what some manapools &quot;might&quot; be.  Ask a lvl 4 newb mage how long it takes him to med from oom to fm, his medskill will be 20 hence he's getting 2mana/tick from meding and 1 mana/tick inate even at that, it's only going to take the lvl 4 a minute or so to be FM.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Right now I have MC 1, FT 2, with c3 and TPP, I get 2% of my mana back a tick. i'm looking at 20% back in a minute. 100 back in 5 minutes.  3300 to 3600 mana.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
From your example:<br>
MC1=1mana/tick; FT2=2mana/tick; KeI=14/tick; TPP=3mana/tick (sorry I haven't found this spell yet); inate=1mana/tick;meditation=20mana/tick.  Your total mana/tick is 41mana/tick.<br>
<br>
If your mana pool is 3300: it will take you 84.48 ticks (lets give it the benefit and say 84 ticks), to go from oom to FM, or 8 minutes 24 seconds. 33 mana is 1% of your manapool so you will get 2% most ticks, 1% on SOME odd ball ticks, you may even see a tick or 2 that shows a 3% jump, which would follow after a 1% tick.<br>
<br>
If your mana pool is 3600: it will take you 87.80 ticks (round down to 87 just to give you the benefit), to go from oom to fm, or 8 minutes 48 seconds.  36 mana would be 1% of your mana pool, so most of the mana increases you'd see would be 1% ticks, with 2% ticks every 4-5 ticks or so.<br>
<br>
Either way, the numbers say your &quot;5 minute&quot; med time is inaccurate.<br>
<br>
Useing KeI +14, Med+ 20, MC3 +3, FT15 +15, inate +1, TPP +3=56mana/tick and your magelo profile of 3521 mana it would take you 62 ticks to go from oom to fm, or 6 minutes 12 seconds, STILL not 5 minutes.<br>
<br>
That is WITH the mana buffs, take those away (per the naked discussion, but leaving your int and +mana items on since I don't know your naked manapool), and you'd only be hitting 21mana/tick, this would take you close to 2 ticks for every 1% mana regen while meding.  Or GENERICALLY 18-20 minutes to med from oom to FM.  <br>
<br>
Either way you look at it, in the time you can summon/reclaim 6 pets, you'd only have gained AT best (without bardsong) 560 mana had you been meditating instead.  6 Pets will get MUCH more than that.  Of course the topic was naked and to the best I could see it would also be w/out all the buffs.  This is why I brought the buffs into it, was to say giving your manapool (which would be smaller NAKED), it would take you 18ish minutes to go from oom to fm w/out buffs.  Given a naked manapool it would take CONSIDERABLY less amount of time.  <br>
<br>
Since an erudite can have 130+int naked (hie can have 128int naked w/out aaint).  Thats greater than 1/2 the int cap, so GENERICALLY (meaning assuming no mana items) you'd cut the naked med time in 1/2.  Which lets just say for your example that would take it down to a little less than 8 minutes medtime.  Either route it's still not the 2 minutes it takes to summon/reclaim to fm.<br>
<br>
If you add in RAz's 5 second pets, you can do 12 pets in a minute, coupled with the savings from spec and efficiency3, your looking at quite a bit of mana savings thus more return for your time.  If you think a 5 minute medtime is good, then you are where I was a week ago.  Since I opened my eyes to canabalizing pets, I see no need to med, other than the ocassional med while waiting on pet to finish a mob.  I am seeing no real need to chain nuke, as we dont have to outdmg our pets, I also really am not needing to chain pets to take down xp mobs, the 52 heal is less mana efficient, but why would I care?  I'll be fm in 2 minutes canabalizing pets.<br>
<br>
Naked, a mage has good mana regen capability, manapool doesn't really matter for taking down xp mobs, unless your dealing with HIGH blues, which really I have no desire to risk death.  I'll continue to take low blues that are STILL blue and NOT light, 3 yellow aaxp in 4 hours IMO isn't that bad, might not be the best but it is enough visual progress that I can remain happy with it.  I am averaging 2 minutes downtime for every 1 blue aaxp, of which is spent canabalizing pets.  BO doesn't have the chance to wear off my pet before I need to start canabalizing so I don't even incur the extra mana cost from having to BO any more than I would have to had I kept 1 pet.  Sure I &quot;might&quot; have to DS pet 3 times, but generally it's only twice.  1 Pet is equalling roughly 1 blue aaxp, I do not see your argument where meding, FT, and your &quot;stated&quot; 5 minute med time, are at all useful.<br>
<br>
Alas, you can continue to get KeI, FT gear, etc and med for your 6-8 Minutes (per the breakdown above-vs-your stated manapool), I'll get a blue aaxp while you med, then i'll get another blue aaxp before you take another med break (since you have manabuffs, FT, etc).  Makes no difference to me, I wish you luck, but in reality throw FT15, MC3 and KeI on me and I &quot;might&quot; get 2-3 more kills out of each pet, or about .00000000004 of a blue (slight exageration, but you get the point), I will still have to eat pets, and possibly throw in a few charges of a t-rod health permitting.<br>
<br>
I even stated I would probably be taken the wrong way, and stated if KeI, FT was readily available I wouldn't turn it down.  If it's going to take me more than 5 minutes to get a KeI though (via zoning, running, etc) then sorry I'll go without, I could have gotten 1/2 a blue aaxp in that 5 minutes, and when it's time to cana the pets all KeI will save me is 1-2 pets (10-20 seconds), which isn't an issue to me at all, since I have no downtime where I am ACTUALLY meditating.  If I were meditating, I would definately want KeI and FT, but without having a need to meditate they are meaningless to me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usampox.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sampox</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 292<br> <font color=#333333>(9/17/02 9:32:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=980.topic&index=27>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hehe</span><hr size=1> people actually still waste points on mental clarity???<br>
